title: FACT SHEET: URGENT RELIEF TO CENTRAL AMERICA | The White House
content: FACT SHEET: URGENT RELIEF TO CENTRAL AMERICAIn light of the dire situation and acute suffering faced by millions of people in El Salvador, Guatemala, and Honduras, Vice President Harris announced an additional $310 million in U.S. government support for humanitarian relief and to address food insecurity. Humanitarian Relief ($255M) Assistance to Address Food Insecurity ($55M)
